info.headline: High Surf Advisory issued November 25 at 1:51AM PST until November 27 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM PST MONDAY... * WHAT...Large breaking waves of 8 to 11 feet with dangerous rip currents. Minor tidal overflow and coastal flooding possible around the time of the morning high tides. * WHERE...San Luis Obispo County Beaches and Santa Barbara County Central Coast Beaches. * WHEN...Until 1 PM PST Monday. * IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and rocks, and capsize small boats near shore. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Minor coastal flooding is possible during the morning high tides of 6.9 to 7.1 feet ranging from 744 AM on Saturday morning to 851 AM on Monday morning.
info.instruction: Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or stay near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in such conditions, stay off the rocks.
